```{=html}
<div class="center">
<p>
<strong>The BBC has revealed its list of 100 inspiring and influential women from around the world for 2020.</strong>
</p>
<div>
<p>This year 100 Women is highlighting those who are leading change and making a difference during these turbulent times.</p>
<p>The list includes Sanna Marin, who leads Finland's all-female coalition government, Michelle Yeoh, star of the new Avatar and Marvel films and Sarah Gilbert, who heads the Oxford University research into a coronavirus vaccine, as well as Jane Fonda, a climate activist and actress.</p>
<p>And in an extraordinary year, when countless women around the world have made a sacrifice to help others, the first place on the list is left open to acknowledge their work and to remember those who have lost their lives while making a difference.</p>
</div>
</div>
